# Learned Memory

## Learned User Preferences

- Always respond in Korean; all generated documents (DOCX, PPTX, markdown reviews) must be entirely in Korean — English is allowed only for proper nouns and technical terms with no standard Korean translation
- Plans and skill definitions (SKILL.md) should be written in English when explicitly requested ("영어로 계획해줘")
- Use clear, assertive wording in docs; include step-by-step calculation formulas with explicit variable substitution, assumption sources, and "why this value" justifications — bare tables without derivation context are insufficient
- Follow professional, concise, technically precise doc style (reference: `01-sellable-services-catalog.md`); no ASCII box-drawing characters — use tables and hierarchical bullets for PDF/Notion compatibility
- Documents must be self-contained — no cross-references like "see document X"; each doc must stand alone when delivered externally
- TDD documents must clearly separate as-is from to-be; after creating cost/pricing documents, always verify calculation accuracy and cross-reference consistency
- Use "Slurm-on-K8s (Slinky)" terminology; clearly separate deployment modes (standalone k0s vs Thaki Suite); RACI framing should emphasize ThakiCloud doing more (investment-positive)
- Content must be substantive and detailed, never skeleton or template-only output; attribute data to source (author, date, repositories)
- Slack notifications go to `#효정-할일` channel (ID: `C0AA8NT4T8T`) — never send to DM; use threaded replies (main summary first, then individual items in thread)
- After creating or modifying a skill, always test it end-to-end and fix issues before declaring done; also create the corresponding Cursor command if one doesn't exist
- When Notion API cannot upload binary files (DOCX/PPTX), adapt content as structured sub-pages instead; Notion API does not support pipe tables — use bulleted lists or HTML table blocks
- Subagent-generated files must be verified after completion — missing output files are a pipeline failure

